      "content": "Ciprofloxacin (Cipro) is an antibiotic, and while it's not typically used for sinus infections, it's important to be cautious about using leftover antibiotics. Taking antibiotics when they're not needed can contribute to antibiotic resistance and may not be effective against your current symptoms. Sinus infections are often viral, and antibiotics won't help unless there's a bacterial infection, which is less common. It's best to avoid self-medicating with leftover antibiotics. Instead, focus on relieving your symptoms with safe methods and consult your healthcare provider as soon as possible. Your health and the health of your baby are the top priorities.",
      "source": "target",
